<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xml:id="idg-all-userguide-create_network-xml-1"><title>&kw-hos-tm; &kw-hos-version-50;: Creating a Private Network</title>
    <!---->


    <sidebar xml:id="idg-all-userguide-create_network-xml-6"><title>Prerequisites</title><para>These steps assume the following have been completed:</para>
<itemizedlist>
        <listitem><para>Your Administrator has created a valid external network for your environment. See <xref linkend="create_extnet"/> for more details.</para>
</listitem>
        <listitem><para>Your Administrator has provided you with the IP address or hostname for the Horizon
          Dashboard. See <xref linkend="cloudadmin_gui"/> for more details.</para>
</listitem>
      </itemizedlist><para>You will want to use the user credentials that your Administrator has provided to you when
        you access the dashboard.</para>
</sidebar>
    <sidebar xml:id="create_router"><title>Creating a Router</title><orderedlist>
          <listitem><para>Access Horizon and log in with your credentials. Contact your Administrator if you do
            not know your login credentials.</para>
</listitem>
          <listitem><para>Open the Create Router wizard by following these steps: </para>
<orderedlist>
              <listitem><para>Navigate to <emphasis role="bold">Routers</emphasis> under the Network menu.</para>
</listitem>
              <listitem><para>Click on the <emphasis role="bold">Create Router</emphasis> button.</para>
</listitem>
            </orderedlist><mediaobject><imageobject  role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_router30_2.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject  role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_router30_2.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
          <listitem><para>Give your router a name and then click the Create Router button again: </para>
<orderedlist>
              <listitem><para>Select a <emphasis role="bold">Router Name</emphasis>.</para>
</listitem>
              <listitem><para>Select an <emphasis role="bold">External Network</emphasis> from the drop down menu.</para>
</listitem>
              <listitem><para>Click on the <emphasis role="bold">Create Router</emphasis> button.</para>
</listitem>
            </orderedlist><mediaobject><imageobject  role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_router30_3.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject  role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_router30_3.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
        </orderedlist>
</sidebar>
    <sidebar xml:id="idg-all-userguide-create_network-xml-8"><title>Creating a Network and Subnet</title><orderedlist>
        <listitem><para>Access Horizon and log in with your credentials. Contact your Administrator if you do
          not know your login credentials.</para>
</listitem>
        <listitem><para>Open the Create Network wizard by following these steps: </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Navigate to <emphasis role="bold">Networks</emphasis> under the Network menu.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Click on the <emphasis role="bold">Create Network</emphasis> button.</para>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist><mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_2.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_2.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
        <listitem><para>On the first window of the create network wizard: </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Choose a <emphasis role="bold">Network Name</emphasis>.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Select the <emphasis role="bold">Next</emphasis> button.</para>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist><mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_3.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_3.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
        <listitem><para>On the second window of the create network wizard: </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Choose a <emphasis role="bold">Subnet Name</emphasis>.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Enter a <emphasis role="bold">Network Address</emphasis> (CIDR) for your subnet.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Select the <emphasis role="bold">Next</emphasis> button.</para>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist><mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_4.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_4.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
        <listitem><para>On the final window of the create network wizard: </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Ensure that <emphasis role="bold">Enable DHCP</emphasis> is checked.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>For a basic network setup, leave the <emphasis role="bold">Allocation Pools</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold">DNS Name
                Servers</emphasis>, and <emphasis role="bold">Host Routes</emphasis> fields blank.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Create</emphasis> when finished.</para>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist><mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_5.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_5.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
        <listitem><para>Next step is to attach your subnet to your router. </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Navigate to <emphasis role="bold">Routers</emphasis> under the Network menu. </para>
<mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_6.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_6.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Click on your router name to bring up its settings. </para>
<mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_7.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_7.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Create the interface by: </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Select the <emphasis role="bold">Interfaces</emphasis> tab.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Click the <emphasis role="bold">Add Interface</emphasis> button.
              </para>
<mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_8.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_8.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Complete the interface creation by: </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Select your subnet from the drop down menu.</para>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>select the <emphasis role="bold">Add Interface</emphasis> button.
              </para>
<mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_9.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_9.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist><warning><para>Do not enter a value for the <literal>IP Address (Optional)</literal>
            field as this can cause other issues.</para>
</warning></listitem>
        <listitem><para>To confirm your router is setup properly you can: </para>
<orderedlist>
            <listitem><para>Click on the <emphasis role="bold">Network Topology</emphasis> menu option: </para>
<mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_10.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_10.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
            <listitem><para>Ensure it looks similar to the screenshot below: </para>
<mediaobject><imageobject role="fo"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_11.png" width="75%" format="PNG"/></imageobject><imageobject role="html"><imagedata fileref="media-networking-create_network30_11.png"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
</listitem>
          </orderedlist></listitem>
      </orderedlist></sidebar>
  </section>
